2007. NET NATURAL-GAS PRODUCTION OF 3.6 BILLION CUBIC FEET PER DAY IN 2009 WAS DOWN 1 PERCENT AND

UP 8 PERCENT FROM 2008 AND 2007, RESPECTIVELY.

